<h5>
Ooty, Tamil Nadu
</h5>
<p>

Established as a summer retreat by the British and nicknamed â€˜Snooty Ooty',Ooty is a visual delight filled with pretty cottages, fenced flower gardens, thatched-roof churches and terraced botanical gardens. Venture a few kilometres out and you'll find yourself surrounded by greener, quieter areas dotted with an abundance of pine trees.

</p>
<p>

<b>Top sightseeing spots:</b> Pykara Falls and Lake, Mudumalai, Doddabetta, Tea Estate Viewpoint, Wax Museum, Hidden Valley, Echo Rock and Emerald Dam.

</p><p>

<b>For how long:</b> Visit Ooty for a period of 3-4 days.

</p><p>

<b>How to reach:</b> Coimbatore is the nearest domestic airport from Ooty located 88 kilometres away from the latter. It is well-connected with most of the Indian cities. The nearest railhead is Mettupalyam situated 40 kilometres from Ooty.
